    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-08-29T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-08-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Breckinridge</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-08-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 29, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.
                                (Received Sept. 17.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 135.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my No. 130, in regard to John
                            Ginzberg, I now have to say that I am informed by a note from Mr.
                            Chichkine that the foreign office has been informed by the ministry of
                            justice that the necessary steps have been taken to hasten the progress
                            of his case.</p>
                <p>The appeal to the minister of the interior to dismiss the case is still
                            pending.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clifton R. Breckinridge.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
